HEADWORD: Seismography
<hw>Seis*mog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
writing about, or a description of, earthquakes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The art of registering the shocks and undulatory
movements of earthquakes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seismological</ent>⟦br⟧
